00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:02.940
Dr. Thompson has authored
many articles and books,

00:01:02.940 --> 00:01:06.840
including "The Embodied
Mind" and "Mind and Life."

00:01:06.840 --> 00:01:10.020
His most recent work is
"Waking, Dreaming, Being,"

00:01:10.020 --> 00:01:13.280
a thought-provoking book
centered around the questions

00:01:13.280 --> 00:01:15.200
what is consciousness?

00:01:15.200 --> 00:01:17.720
How does it relate to
the brain and body?

00:01:17.720 --> 00:01:20.520
How does it relate
to our sense of self?

00:01:20.520 --> 00:01:22.240
The book has been
widely praised.

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:24.450
It's been called a
groundbreaking exploration

00:01:24.450 --> 00:01:26.460
of consciousness.

00:01:26.460 --> 00:01:28.900
Dr. Richard Davidson,
researcher and founder

00:01:28.900 --> 00:01:31.750
of the Center for
Healthy Minds, comments,

00:01:31.750 --> 00:01:33.580
"It is a dazzling synthesis.

00:01:33.580 --> 00:01:36.610
Thompson takes on some of the
most fundamental questions

00:01:36.610 --> 00:01:38.920
about the nature of
mind, and addresses them

00:01:38.920 --> 00:01:42.750
with remarkable
creativity and clarity.

00:01:42.750 --> 00:01:45.870
This volume is a must-read for
any serious student of the mind

00:01:45.870 --> 00:01:47.120
and consciousness."

00:01:47.120 --> 00:01:50.274
And I can say I've read
it and I've enjoyed it.

00:01:50.274 --> 00:01:52.190
There are many fascinating
things in the book.

00:01:52.190 --> 00:01:55.190
So I recommend you read it, too.

00:01:55.190 --> 00:01:58.770
And now I'll turn it over
to Professor Thompson

00:01:58.770 --> 00:02:00.680
to guide us on a
stimulating journey

00:02:00.680 --> 00:02:05.605
through "Waking,
Dreaming, and Being."

00:02:05.605 --> 00:02:09.070
